    <div class="lesson-content-memo"> Partially particle; wave on Wednesdays </div> 
    <div class="col-md-6 col-lg-6">
      Light is a wave propagation phenomenon of the electromagnetic (EM) radiation field.
        For any wave: 
        <ul>
            <li>Speed = Frequency x Wavelength</li>
            <li>c = f λ</li>
        </ul>

        An EM wave can interact with matter (atoms, electrons).
        These interactions take place by means of energy quanta of size: E = h f.
        Each quantum also transfers a definite amount of momentum: 
        p=h/λ      (from E=pc, so p=E/c = hf/c = h/λ).

        Photons do not have definite trajectories, although often this can be ignored.
    </div>
      
